onsibilities and to make the "right" choices -- and we beat ourselves up when we fail, as Princeton professor Anne-Marie Slaughter, the former director of policy planning for the State Department, [[http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2012/07/why-women-still-can-8217-t-have-it-all/9020/ |  wrote in this month's ''Atlantic ''cover story ]] . "Millions of women feel that they are to blame if they cannot manage to rise up the ladder as fast as men and also have a family and an active home life (and be thin and beautiful to boot)," she wrote. And unsurprisingly, perhaps, women suffer from a number of anxiety disorders -- including generalized anxiety and panic attacks -- at a rate twice as high as that for men.%0a> %0a62,64c198,203%0a%3c %0a%3c !!'''We all have too many choices '''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> \\%0a> %0a> ''''''%0a> %0a> '''We all have too many choices '''%0a> %0a73,74c212,217%0a%3c !!'''But we don't all have the ''same'' choices'''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> \\%0a> %0a> ''''''%0a> %0a> '''But we don't all have the ''same'' choices'''%0a> %0a79,80c222,227%0a%3c !!'''The Obama example, and genetics'''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> \\%0a> %0a> ''''''%0a> %0a> '''The Obama example, and genetics'''%0a> %0a85,86c232,235%0a%3c !!''' What the recession demonstrates about luck'''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> \\%0a> %0a> ''' What the recession demonstrates about luck'''%0a> %0a91,93c240,243%0a%3c %0a%3c !!'''Dealing with anxiety in a meritocracy'''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> \\%0a> %0a> ''' ''' '''Dealing with anxiety in a meritocracy'''%0a> %0a99a250,417%0a>  \\%0a>  \\%0a> [[http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php |  http://cdn.theatlantic.com/static/front/images/icons/social/share.gif Share ]] [[http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php | ]] [[http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php | ]] [[http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php | ]] [[http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php |  http://cdn.theatlantic.com/static/front/images/icons/social/email.gif Email ]] [[http://www.theatlantic.com/health/print/2012/07/trickle-down-distress-ho